00:00:27,560 --> 00:00:31,200
 So inheritance actually from that lecture

9
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:34,840
 is the notion in object-oriented programming to not repeat yourself.

10
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:41,200
 You have some kind of a shape and then you make a bunch of objects that mirror

11
00:00:41,200 --> 00:00:45,320
 that shape, but you can also with inheritance you can have a shape that

12
00:00:45,320 --> 00:00:49,320
 makes another shape like a shape in general that's a triangle.

13
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:52,520
 And so you can inherit that all triangles have everything shapes have and

14
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:56,080
 all squares have everything shapes have and all circles.

15
00:00:56,080 --> 00:00:59,920
 And it's just a way of capturing information once,

16
00:00:59,920 --> 00:01:03,080
 writing code once and then not repeating yourself.

17
00:01:03,080 --> 00:01:08,840
 Functions are a form of DRY, don't repeat yourself, modules are.

18
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:14,160
 But inheritance is the key and inheritance kinda can get in our way as programmers

19
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:17,960
 because it leads to smaller and smaller code.

20
00:01:17,960 --> 00:01:22,000
 If we're gonna make five things, each of these five things is really small because

