00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:11,960
 So template rendering basically says, okay,

35
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:14,160
 here's some rendered data and here's a template.

36
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:18,600
 What happens now is there's this thing called a base template.

37
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:22,240
 And the base template and the template combine together to be sort of like

38
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:25,880
 the ultimate template, and then you pass in the rendered data and

39
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:27,680
 produce the rendered output.

40
